@REC-01 

Write a Java program to check whether a given string is a palindrome using recursion.

A palindrome is a string that reads the same forward and backward.

Examples
Input	Output
"abba"	true
"madam"	true
"abc"	false
"" (empty string)	true
 Approach (Recursive Two-Pointer Technique)

We use two pointers:

l → starting index

r → ending index

Steps:

Base Case

If l >= r, all characters are checked → return true

Mismatch Case

If s.charAt(l) != s.charAt(r) → return false

Recursive Case

Move inward:

isPalindrome(s, l + 1, r - 1)



CODE : 
// string is palindrome is or  ot using recursion 
import java.util.*;
public class Main
{
    public static boolean ispalindrome(String s , int l , int r )
    {
      
      if(l>=r)
      {
          return true ;
      }
      if(s.charAt(l)!=s.charAt(r))
      return false;
     return ispalindrome(s,l+1,r-1);
    }
   public static boolean callingfunction(String s , int l , int r)
   {
      return ispalindrome(s,0 , s.length()-1);
   }
	public static void main(String[] args) {
	//	System.out.println("Hello World");
	String s = "";
	int r = s.length();
	boolean ans = callingfunction(s ,0, r);
	System.out.println(ans);
	}
}
